sentences: Chinedu Okoli (born 23 November 1983), better known by his stage name Flavour N'abania or simply Flavour, is a Nigerian singer, songwriter and multi-instrumentalist.
In 2005, he released his self-titled debut album N'abania.
In 2010, Flavour released his second studio album, Uplifted.
In 1996, Flavour was invited to join the company on an educational scholarship to study music.
In 1999, he moved on from playing the drums and started playing the keyboard.
=== 2005: N'abania
In 2005, Flavour released his debut album N'abania through Obaino Music.
Following the relative success of his debut album, Flavour released Uplifted in 2010.
Blessed was released on 18 October 2012 through 2nite Entertainment and iROCKING LTD.
Thankful was released in December 2014.
Ijele – The Traveller was released in 2017.
In 2018 Flavour issued two singles, "Crazy love", joining forces with Mama Africa Yemi Alade as Flavour Nabania, and "Yemi Alade".
On 29 August 2012, Nigerian Entertainment Today reported that Flavour was involved in a legal battle with Ghanaian duo Wutah, over the alleged theft of "Kwarikwa".
